5:
Salty waters, salty air... Hot sand and
hot sun...
7:
VR could never get you this much
sensory info!
10:
It looks like upping your outfit's heat
resistance parameters was the right
call.
14:
Haha, if you ever came here in
person, we'd have to lather you in
sunblock.
18:
Oh. I see you two joined us on our
vacation this year.
22:
Sera? I didn't know you were here
too.
26:
I am here every year on request, as
they never have enough lifeguards
on duty.
30:
Bulleta, since when were you such
good friends with Sera?
34:
Remember how me and her teamed
up together when all that crap was
going down in Qualia City? We
started talking after that.
41:
S-Sera's got a partner of her own, so
we swap advice sometimes...
49:
I will be heading back to my patrol.
By the way... I highly recommend
watching the sunset on the beach.
55:
Er... She's a workaholic too, but she
loves what she does, y'know?
59:
I'll also be working hard when I get
back. As your Bullet, I can't give
anything less than a hundred
percent.
63:
Could you quit calling yourself that?
You should be your—
66:
Sorry, I'm just venting my
frustrations out on you. I need a
moment.
77:
I can't tell what's going through
Love's head at all!
81:
Raaagh! Damn it, I need another
pint over here!
89:
Are you sure you should be drinking
so much?
93:
Oh, shut it. I can clear the alcohol
from my system in three seconds
and go for a run if I have to.
96:
I want to be Love's Bullet, but she
doesn't seem to love the idea. I can't
figure out why.
98:
...I just want to be strong enough to
stand by her side.
107:
Maybe for the average person? But
honestly, I feel like it depends on the
person.
112:
I-I don't think it's wrong to want to
be on equal footing with someone
you care about.
116:
It always motivates me to try harder
when I watch my coworkers and
friends at work!
119:
Pythica... You're a good person, you
know that?
122:
...I wonder how I'm gonna face her
after this.
127:
You should treat her like you always
do.
131:
But don't you think I'm being a
bother?
135:
Hmm... You said she seemed upset,
right?
146:
We've had this conversation before,
right? Is this something you want
others to decide for you?
150:
Sheesh, you can be real mean when
you want to be...
155:
Unlike back then, however, I believe
you've already come to a decision.
164:
But first, I'm gonna stuff myself full!
Gotta load the chamber before I fire
off!
167:
Then I'm gonna drag Love out from
wherever she's hiding!
174:
...Do you rule over the night even on
the beach?
177:
Here, in a world different from ours? I
hadn't given it any thought.
181:
Be honest, Love. Do you not need me
anymore?
189:
You're making waves, you know.
Charging full speed ahead. But me?
I'm struggling to keep up.
192:
I figured that if I wanted to support
you, I could be your Bullet—clear the
path ahead and give you an
opening...
196:
...Was that your goal all along? You
idiot.
199:
You don't need to worry about me.
I'd rather you stay the Bullet of
Freedom and do what YOU want to
do.
202:
After all, that's the kind of person
that saved a lost, lonely girl like me
and gave her someone to love.
206:
...Looking back on it now, it's kinda
embarrassing how far I flew off the
handle.
209:
But you're... You're right. From the
beginning, it didn't matter who we
were or the skills we had...
212:
Or whether or not we're fit for each
other.
215:
That's right. We're a team despite it
all.
223:
I was overthinking everything, huh?
Sorry, Love.
226:
...There is just one thing I wanna
make clear though.
229:
I made the choice to support you of
my own volition.
233:
I want to be your Bullet, because I
want to be. Simple as that. Won't
you let me?
237:
Do you even need to ask? You're
already my partner. You may as well
be my Bullet too.
243:
That aside... Care to explain why you
were so familiar with Sera this
afternoon?
251:
Hold on, is that what you were mad
about this whole time? Just that?
258:
You really don't understand a thing,
do you?!
266: I was in the wrong! Partneeeer!
